1. ViewData
✔️ Works only for current request
✔️ Key/value dictionary
✔️ Requires casting
✔️ Used to pass data from Controller → View
ViewData["Message"] = "Hello ViewData";
return View();
in the View:
@ViewData["Message"]

2. ViewBag
✔️ Works only for current request
✔️ Uses dynamic object
✔️ No casting required
✔️ Just a wrapper around ViewData
ViewBag.Message = "Hello ViewBag";
return View();
In the View:
@ViewBag.Message

3. TempData
✔️ Persists across requests
✔️ Used for RedirectToAction scenarios
✔️ Good for showing success/error messages
✔️ Uses session storage under the hood
TempData["Success"] = "Saved!";
return RedirectToAction("Index");
In the next request:
@TempData["Success"]
